<br>
Anyways, I started playing again last week to check out Ldon, and make sure my account wasn't deleted. And well, EQ has gone through alot of changes, but the one change for the worse I see, that everquest is no longer hard. I mean, it used to take a WEEK to level, now, I can easily get a level a day 60+ or 2 aaxp points, in SUCKY pickup groups with no class balance. <br>
<br>
Does it irk anyone else that SoE has basically dumbed down the entire game to nothing now. Everquest no longer has any kind of skill, all it is now is a game of time... the more time you play, the better your stuff, now with Ldon that is set in stone. No longer if you know what your doing, and play better than any other person will you be able to be one of &quot;the best&quot; all it comes down to now is time. All the high end raids now have timers, because the stuff is TOO EASY now. <br>
<br>
Tanks having 10k HP, casters having 7k, Hello what has happened to EQ,  has it devolved into nothing but a giant timesink that you pay for ? <br>
<br>
Mana is no longer even a worry. I remember when I played a cleric in the end game(pre SoL) I had to time my dam cheals to get the most possible healing and mana effieciency. Now, nothing like that even remotely comes close to that, clerics fire off a bazillion different heal spells anytime they want without having to worry about not having enough mana. Every character is so stacked to the gills with HP items that wizards have 4000 unbuffed HP, remember when freaking furor and only the big guild warriors had this much?<br>
<br>
No longer can the casual players compete with the heavy players, because now more than ever time <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>TIME = EQUIPMENT/SKILL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Sure, it was always like that, where the people who played the most would have the best, but for the average guy who wasn't in the uber guild of the server, if you were good, and knew the quests, knew the zones, and weren't a nooby you could compete with those guys by using your knowledge.<br>
<br>
Now, with LDoN that has been taken completely away. Basically now all it comes down to is, how much you play, and what items you buy with your points. Whats even more sad is that now, those adventures are an utter joke of ease. I mean honestly, these aren't dungeon crawls, they are time sinks with EXP that is so easy to get. Dungeon crawls have a sense of danger, this is just a sick joke, a half assed unbalanced group of schmoes, with at least 1 healer can easily beat any of these adv, time is the only thing that even comes close to defeating anyone.<br>
<br>
Maybe its just me, but who else would like to see actual PLAYER SKILL have some visible effect on the game. Right now the only thing that matters is time and to be honest I don't think anyone should have to spend 40 hours a week playing this game to be able to compete. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=irexes>Irexes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scythe matters<br>
