Ya what is this competition you are talking of?<br>
<br>
The leader board for LDoN?<br>
<br>
<br>
IMO, the game was fun before many of the changes, and the game is more fun after the last few expansions.<br>
<br>
IMO, there was so much more downtime before SoL and the portal system it brought, then PoP and the book portal system it brought.<br>
<br>
Though you didn't mention it, I welcome the transportation systems, and I welcome the alternative ways to earn very nice loot than raiding (LDoN).<br>
<br>
Yes points are earned faster for higher level players, and it would make sense that it would considering some of the very nice gear you can buy with a decent amount of points.<br>
<br>
EQ was always a time sink.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have not mentioned how &quot;hard&quot; the game was. because honestly, the game was not a &quot;hard&quot; or &quot;easy&quot; thing.  <br>
<br>
Coordinating people for a raid and trying to keep peace with people are the hardest things for many in EQ.  Sure there are many who do not know how to play there class.  There always were.<br>
<br>
None of this has anything to do with the workings of the game, but rather communication and organization with strangers, and the ability to put up with people who do not know how to play their class.<br>
<br>
It is game, sometimes its more fun than other times.<br>
<br>
Perhaps they raised the reward systems so that you can get better gear with less periods of waiting and camping.<br>
<br>
I'll tell you, a larger factor to the prevalence of really nice gear to lower level players is the lack of No-Drop on this server, and not what you consider &quot;dumbing down the game&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you really like the old zones so much, they are still there.  You don't have to play LDoN or PoP.<br>
<br>
And believe it or not skill (or cooperation) are still needed to do well in LDoN.  If you don't play your class well or don't work well with your group, you may get your group killed or not complete your mission in time.<br>
<br>
<br>
If I had a Larraque picture to stamp this thread.  I would dub this rant, weak and not very well thought out.<br>
<br>
You are pissed off at something, but if the changes are that crappy, you also have the option not to play.<br>
<br>
I personally don't miss taking boats to continents, and spending hours or days on a quest to get a crappy weapon that is underrated for the creatures you should be killing at your level.<br>
<br>
I believe the game is moving away from that, but I could be wrong.<br>
