<br>
I remember when you could be in a group for a week to get level 52 ..... then level 53 was harder still.  <br>
<br>
I watched a Druid in our guild solo his way from 51 through 65 in about a week and a half without even really trying too hard in the PoN.   Bah!  How can you respect a player like that??  At least in the old days when you saw a level 60 player you knew they had busted their ass to get there.  <br>
<br>
The game has changed so much since then, and personally I think it's a lot more interesting now than it was then with so many more zones to explore, and dungeons to crawl .... but I can see the original posters point about how easy it is now to be 'ubah' ... especially on Firiona Vie where you can buy Vindi BP's and better in the bazaar if you farm enough plat.  <br>
<br>
The content has moved on so much now that it is saddening to hear about people soloing Vox and Naggy because of the gear they have.... heh.   <br>
<br>
They have also, however, increased the difficulty in a number of places like Velks and Sebilis so that you can go deeper in at level 65 and enjoy a romp that isn't simplistically easy... at least for a level 65 Bard with only a few aa's and who doesn't have a million hp's .... lol... and where you can also gain experience. <br>
<br>
If the game hadn't moved on from the old days of pre-luclin, then how would people keep moving forward onto harder and harder things?  The level 60's of old would have quit and Sony would have lost a bunch of subscriptions!!!  <br>
<br>
This said, I do agree that it's too easy to level 60-65 ... it would be nice if they could have more solo/single group questable items that were actually worth getting.... and it would be nice if experience wasn't sooo good in PoP so that people were encouraged to journey around the world some more! <br>
<br>
(Oh, and I also miss boats... and think the spires and more recently the books have been hugely detrimental to the EQ experience).... <br>
<br>
