<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqpixelarmy.com/" target="top">Cannon Fodder for the EQPA!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kebkin>Kebkin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 269<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/03 3:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4101.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Say what?</span><hr size=1> I've been playing EQ since the first week it was released.  In the early stages of the game, there were no class boards or spoiler sites.  Those didn't become prominent until later when folks discovered EZboards.  So for the most part, your knowledge of how the game worked was limited to what you had actually experienced for yourself.<br>
<br>
I played a bard as my first character.  At the time, there were not that many enchanters around because folks hadn't yet realized how powerful crowd control was.  Folks also did not really understand how aggro worked.  As a result, I ended up dying quite a bit.  Bard songs that affected the entire group were major aggro magnets. On every pull that had 2 or more mobs in it, all of the adds ended up attacking me.   As a result, I would die on average at least 10 times between levels.  I remember level 25 very clearly.  It took me like 2 months to get through it because I died close to 20 times (Mistmoore trains are the best).  <br>
<br>
It wasn't until folks learned how aggro worked and discovered the power of enchanters that I stopped dying on a frequent basis.   So I started gaining levels faster since I stopped dying so much.  The game world itself didn't change much in terms of difficulty, the players just got smarter.<br>
<br>
Some of the recent features (ex. PoK portal system) that folks complain about that dumb down the game are just smart moves on SOE's part to retain their customer base.  I don't think their purpose was to make the game explicitly easier, but instead to make it less frustrating.  I know that if I still had to catch a boat to get from one continent to the next I would no longer be playing.  Been there done that too many times.  When I log in now, I just want to hunt with my friends and have fun.     <br>
<br>
There are still numerous places I and my guild can go that provide a difficult challenge for either an EXP group or a raid.   So by no means is the game too easy in that aspect.  However, there are many easy places I can go now if all I want to do is EXP grind for levels or AAs.   However, the same can be said 4 years ago for the original content as well.  Folks will play the game however they want to.  If they want to be challenged, the game provides for that.  If they want a relatively safe ride all the way to 65, the game provides for that as well.    <p>Kebkin <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
